bug in:
http://mxnet.io/tutorials/python/char_lstm.html
```
def Perplexity(label, pred):
    loss = 0.
    for i in range(pred.shape[0]):
        loss += -np.log(max(1e-10, pred[i][int(label[i])]))
    return np.exp(loss / label.size)
```

**The _label_ is a matrix , so it should correct as below :** 
```
def Perplexity(label, pred):
    rows=label.shape[0]
    cols=label.shape[1]
    loss=0
    for i in range(rows):
        for j in range(cols):
            loss += -np.log(max(1e-10, pred[i*cols+j][int(label[i][j])]))
    return np.exp(loss / label.size)
```

