It would be be great if we could define the code for Lambda functions inline. This functionality already exists for AWS::Lambda::Function resources and it is very convenient for things like Custom Resources that execute as part of the CloudFormation template or really simple Lambda@Edge functions.

Of course it would be understood if there needs to be a limit to the number of characters.

E.g. of current usage in a regular CloudFormation template

```
Resources:
  StaticSiteHelper: 
    Type: "AWS::Lambda::Function"
    Description: "Implements index.html support for directories &redirects to add a trailing slash"
    Properties: 
      Handler: "index.handler"
      Role: !GetAtt LambdaRole.Arn
      Code:
        ZipFile: |
          exports.handler = (event, context, callback) => {
            const request = event.Records[0].cf.request;
            const matchArray = request.uri.match(/[^/]+$/);
              
            if (matchArray === null){
              request.uri = request.uri.replace(/\/$/, '\/index.html');        
              return callback(null, request);
            }	
            else if (matchArray[0].includes('.') === false){
              const response = {
                status: '302',
                headers: { location: [{ key: 'Location',value: request.uri + '/' }] }
              };
              return callback(null, response);
            }

            return callback(null, request);
          };
