CircleCI build fails after merging #114 from @JoranHonig, which fixed a bug in `report_test.py` (`output_expected` had been compared to `output_expected` instead of `output_current`).

The failure is likely due a difference in to the `solc` version installed in the CircleCI image, which causes bytecode generated from Solidity files to differ slightly. It is likely that updating `solc` to 0.4.21 fixes the issue.

